<TITLE> Fire at Shankar from electrical short-circuit </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, June 5 (bdnews24.com)  A short fire broke out in two electrical metre-boxes at a building of Shankar, Dhaka on Saturday afternoon. The metre-boxes caught fire at the ground of the five-storey building 'Prabaha' in Jafrabad at around 4pm. It was put out swiftly even before the fire fighters reached the spot. Mohammadpur fire service station officer said the situation was under control but "not quite safe". The electrical wires were jumbled up leading to the metre boxes, next to which lay the building's generator and water pump. The fire service severed electrical connection to prevent further short-circuits. They said that officials from the designated power agencies would fix them later. Given much tension due to the large fire in Old Dhaka which killed almost 120 people on Thursday, locals prepared to leave the area as soon as news of the fire broke out. b
